#: ../../source/api/events.md:1
msgid "Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:3
msgid ""
"Events are methods that Miniworlds calls automatically. Register them on a "
"`World` or an `Actor` with the `@...register` decorator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:6
msgid "Main Loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:18
msgid ""
"`on_setup` runs once before the world starts. `act` runs once per frame "
"while the world is running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:21
msgid "Keyboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:23
msgid "Use a specific key handler when you only care about one key:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:35
msgid ""
"Use a generic handler when you need to inspect the currently pressed keys:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:46
msgid "Keyboard events:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:48
msgid "`on_key_down(self, keys)`: once when a key is pressed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:49
msgid "`on_key_pressed(self, keys)`: every frame while a key is held"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:50
msgid "`on_key_up(self, keys)`: when a key is released"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:51
msgid ""
"`on_key_down_<key>(self)`, `on_key_pressed_<key>(self)`, "
"`on_key_up_<key>(self)`: key-specific handlers without a `keys` parameter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:54
msgid ""
"Common key names include `w`, `a`, `s`, `d`, `space`, `left`, `right`, `up`, "
"and `down`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:57
msgid "Mouse"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:70
msgid "Mouse events:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:72
msgid ""
"`on_mouse_left(self, position)`, `on_mouse_right(self, position)`, "
"`on_mouse_middle(self, position)`: while a button is held"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:74
msgid ""
"`on_mouse_left_down(self, position)`, `on_mouse_left_up(self, position)`: "
"press and release events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:76
msgid "`on_mouse_motion(self, position)`: mouse movement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:77
msgid ""
"`on_clicked(self, position)`, `on_clicked_left(self, position)`, "
"`on_clicked_right(self, position)`: actor click events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:79
msgid ""
"`on_mouse_over(self, position)`, `on_mouse_enter(self, position)`, "
"`on_mouse_leave(self, position)`: actor hover events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:81
msgid ""
"`on_wheel_up(self, position)`, `on_wheel_down(self, position)`: mouse wheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:83
msgid "Sensors And Borders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:95
msgid "Sensor and collision events:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:97
msgid "`on_detecting(self, other)`: any detected actor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:98
msgid "`on_detecting_actor(self, other)`: any actor on the same position"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:99
msgid ""
"`on_detecting_<ClassName>(self, other)`: actors of a specific class, for "
"example `on_detecting_wall`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:101
msgid "`on_not_detecting(self)`: no actor detected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:102
msgid "`on_not_detecting_<ClassName>(self)`: no actor of that class detected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:103
msgid "`on_detecting_world(self)`: actor is inside the world"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:104
msgid "`on_not_detecting_world(self)`: actor is outside the world"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:105
msgid "`on_detecting_not_on_world(self)`: alias for `on_not_detecting_world`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:106
msgid ""
"`on_detecting_borders(self, borders)`: receives a list like `[\"left\"]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:107
msgid ""
"`on_detecting_left_border(self)`, `on_detecting_right_border(self)`, "
"`on_detecting_top_border(self)`, `on_detecting_bottom_border(self)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:110
msgid ""
"Both `on_not_detecting_world` and `on_detecting_not_on_world` are accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:112
msgid "Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:114
msgid ""
"Messages are useful when actors should communicate without holding direct "
"references to each other."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:127
msgid ""
"Use `send_message(message, data=None)` to broadcast a message. Use "
"`@actor.register_message(\"message\")` or "
"`@world.register_message(\"message\")` to react to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:131
msgid "Focus"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:133
msgid "Actors can react when they receive or lose focus after a click:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:135
msgid "`on_focus(self)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/events.md:136
msgid "`on_focus_lost(self)`"
msgstr ""
